GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 1
HOUSE BILL 1187
Short Title: Save Our Beaches. (Public)
Sponsors: Representatives Harrison, Butler, Greenfield, and Cook (Primary Sponsors).
For a complete list of sponsors, refer to the North Carolina General Assembly web site.
Referred to: Agriculture and Environment, if favorable, State and Local Government, if
favorable, Rules, Calendar, and Operations of the House
May 5, 2026
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO DISAPPROVE A RULE RELATED TO THE USE OF WHEAT STRAW BALES
3 FOR SAND FENCING IN OCEAN HAZARD AREAS.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. Pursuant to G.S. 150B-21.3(b1), the amendment to 15A NCAC 07H
6 .0314 (Installation and Maintenance of Wheat Straw Bales for Sand Fencing in Ocean Hazard
7 Areas), as adopted by the North Carolina Coastal Resources Commission on April 30, 2025, and
8 approved by the Rules Review Commission on June 26, 2025, is disapproved.
9 SECTION 2. This act is effective when it becomes law.
